            "body": "> watchfiles uses `vim.glob`:\r\n> \r\n> https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/9f468a0b5fba9b0284bf0ce407c3f44af2ce3fc2/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_watchfiles.lua#L2\r\n> \r\n> does `vim.glob` return the correct result for your input? This note may be related:\r\n> \r\n> https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/9f468a0b5fba9b0284bf0ce407c3f44af2ce3fc2/test/functional/lua/glob_spec.lua#L67-L77\r\n\r\nyes, vim.glob works.. I maybe it is filewatcher broken?\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal glob = vim.glob;\r\n\r\nlocal match = function(pattern, str)\r\n    return glob.to_lpeg(pattern):match(str) ~= nil\r\nend\r\n\r\nprint(match(\"**/CMakeCache.txt\", \"./build/CMakeCache.txt\"))\r\n\r\n```",
